sentences: Jessica Jung (born Jessica Sooyoun Jung; April 18, 1989), also known by the mononym Jessica, is a  Korean-American singer, songwriter, actress, novelist, and businesswoman known for her work as a former member of South Korean girl group Girls' Generation.
As an actress, Jung portrayed Elle Woods in the Korean version of the musical Legally Blonde in 2010 and played a role in the television drama Wild Romance in 2012.

In early 2014, she established a fashion brand, Blanc & Eclare.

Her debut best-selling novel Shine was released in September 2020.
While on vacation in South Korea, she and her sister, Krystal, were spotted in a shopping mall by a member of SM Entertainment; she later joined the company in 2000.
